elements.description:
# The API Console

The API console for RAML (Restful Api Modeling Language) documents.
The RAML Console allows browsing of API documentation and in-browser testing of API methods.

properties.name: amfModel
properties.description:
Generated AMF json/ld model form the API spec.
The element assumes the object of the first array item to be a
type of `"http://raml.org/vocabularies/document#Document`
on AMF vocabulary.

It is only usefult for the element to resolve references.

properties.name: ns
properties.description: A namespace for AMF model

properties.name: aware
properties.description:
You can use `raml-aware` component to pass AMF data to the console.
Raml aware uses monostate pattern to pass the data to any other
instance of the same component and receives updates from them.

When using `<raml-aware>` set it's `scope` property to some name
and this property to the same name. Once you update `raml` property
on the aware it updates the model in the console.

properties.name: selectedShape
properties.description:
It is current selection from the navigation represented
as an `@id` property of the AMD json/ld model.

This property is updated internally when the user performs a navigation.
Change this property (with `selectedShapeType` property if needed)
to force the console to render specific view.

## example
```
file://demo/models/api-name/api.raml#/web-api/end-points/%2Ftest-endpoint
```

properties.name: selectedShapeType
properties.description:
One of recognizable bby the console types of currently rendered
documentation. It can be one of:

- summary
- documentation
- type
- security
- endpoint
- method

Use it with combination of setting `selectedShape` property to control
the view.

properties.name: isMethod
properties.description: Computed value, true if current selection represent a method

properties.name: modelLocation
properties.description:
Location of the AMF json/ld model. It can be an endpoint that
produces AMF model or a file that contains generated model.

When changed it download's data from the location
and assigns value to the `amfModel` property.

## Example
```html
<api-console model-location="https://amf-parser/domain.com"></api-console>
```

properties.name: page
properties.description: Currently rendered page. It can be either `docs` or `request`.

properties.name: isRequest
properties.description:
Computed value (read only), `true` when current page is the
request panel.

properties.name: isDocs
properties.description:
Computed value (read only), `true` when current page is the
documentation panel.

properties.name: noExtensionBanner
properties.description:
The API console works with API console extension that proxies
request through Chrome extension's sandbox and eliminates CORS.

The banner informing a user about the extension is rendered
automatically unless this property is set.

properties.name: extensionBannerActive
properties.description: When set the extension banner is rendered.

properties.name: appendHeaders
properties.description:
Forces the console to send headers defined in this string overriding
any used defined header.
It can be useful if the console has to send any headers string
to a server without user knowing about it.
The headers should be valid HTTP headers string.

properties.name: narrow
properties.description:
If true it forces the console to render narrow layout.
This hides left hand side navigation and some fonts are smaller
(like titles).

properties.name: proxy
properties.description:
If set every request made from the console will be proxied by the service provided in this
value.
It will prefix entered URL with the proxy value. so the call to
`http://domain.com/path/?query=some+value` will become
`https://proxy.com/path/http://domain.com/path/?query=some+value`

If the proxy require a to pass the URL as a query parameter define value as follows:
`https://proxy.com/path/?url=`. In this case be sure to set `proxy-encode-url`
attribute.

properties.name: proxyEncodeUrl
properties.description:
If `proxy` is set, it will URL encode the request URL before appending it to the proxy URL.
`http://domain.com/path/?query=some+value` will become
`https://proxy.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fdomain.com%2Fpath%2F%3Fquery%3Dsome%2Bvalue`

properties.name: noTryIt
properties.description:
If set then the API console hide the "try it" button from the
method documentation view. The request and response panels still will
be available, but to enter this section you'll have to do it
programatically.

properties.name: manualNavigation
properties.description:
If set, the open navigation button will be always hidden.
The left hand side navigation will be hidden until `navigationOpened`
property is set.
The navigation will cover full screen, hiding the content.
This works best with `narrow` layout.

properties.name: navigationOpened
properties.description: True when navigation is opened.

properties.name: responsiveWidth
properties.description:
A width when the navigation drawer is automatically toggled to narrow
view.
By default it is `640px`.

To control width of the navigation drawer, set `--app-drawer-width`
CSS variable to requested size.

properties.name: _narrowNavForced
properties.description:
Computed value, true when the navigation drawer should be hidden
event with wide layout.

properties.name: bowerLocation
properties.description:
Location of the `bower_components` folder.
It should be a path from server's root path including bower_components.

properties.name: redirectUri
properties.description:
OAuth2 redirect URI.
By default the app uses `bowerLocation` to compute redirect location
URI. If you set this value if has to work with authorization
component meaning it has to pass auth data to the opener window or
top frame.
See documentation for `advanced-rest-client/oauth-authorization`
for API details.

properties.name: noUrlEditor
properties.description:
Hides the URL editor from the view.
Note that the editor is still in the DOM. This property just hiddes
it.

properties.name: baseUri
properties.description:
A base URI for the API. To be set if RAML spec is missing `baseUri`
declaration and this produces invalid URL input. This information
is passed to the URL editor that prefixes the URL with `baseUri` value
if passed URL is a relative URL.

properties.name: noAttribution
properties.description:
Removes the "Powered by Mulesoft" attribution from the main navigation.
The use of this feature must be in accordance with all licensing
and copyright protections required by the use of this software

properties.name: webApi
properties.description: Computed value of AMF model of a type of `http://schema.org/WebAPI`

properties.name: apiTitle
properties.description: Computed title of the API

properties.name: isChrome
properties.description:
If true then current browser is Chrome.
Used to determine if the console should render the extension banner.

properties.name: layoutNarrow
properties.description:
True when the main layout element renders in narrow view.
This changes when media query breakpoint has been reached or
when narrow property is set.

properties.name: drawerAlign
properties.description:
An alignment of the layout drawer.
Possible values are:
- start
- end

Default to "start".

properties.name: noToolbars
properties.description: If set the top toolbars are not rendered.

properties.name: app
properties.description:
By default API console renders itself as an embeddable
web component that has changed behavior of main layout elements
(menu drawer and main view). When this option is set it renders
layout elements in it's static positions instead relative.

Note, this option is experimental and mey be removed.

properties.name: wideLayout
properties.description:
When true it places try it panel next to the documentation panel.
It is set automatically via media queries

properties.name: inlineMethods
properties.description:
If set then it renders methods documentation inline with
the endpoint documentation.
When it's not set (or value is `false`, default) then it renders
just a list of methods with links in the documentation panel

properties.name: methodName
properties.description:
Computed value from the method model, name of the method.
It is either a `displayName` or HTTP method name

properties.name: scrollTarget
properties.description:
Scroll target used to observe `scroll` events.
Set it to a parent element that is a scroll region (has overflow set)
so the app can handle scrolling properly.

properties.name: allowDisableParams
properties.description:
Option passed to the try it panel.
When set it allows to disable parameters in an editor (headers,
query parameters). Disabled parameter won't be used with a test call
but won't be removed from the UI.

properties.name: allowCustom
properties.description:
Option passed to the try it panel.
When set, editors renders "add custom" button that allows to define
custom parameters next to API spec defined.

properties.name: allowHideOptional
properties.description:
Option passed to the try it panel.
Enables auto hiding of optional properties (like query parameters
or headers) and renders a checkbox to render optional items in the
editor view.

properties.name: noDocs
properties.description:
Prohibits rendering documentation (the icon and the
description) in request editors.

properties.name: eventsTarget
properties.description:
A HTML element used to listen for events on.
If you use one than more API console elements on single page
at the same time wrap the console is a HTML element (eg div) and
set this value to the container so the request panel only listen
to events dispatched inside the container. Otherwise events dispatched
by the request panel will be handled by other instances of the console.

methods.name: _getAmfKey
methods.description: Returns compact model key for given value.

return.desc:
Compact model property name or the same value if
value not found in the context.

methods.name: _ensureAmfModel
methods.description: Ensures that the model is AMF object.

methods.name: _ensureArray
methods.description:
Ensures that the value is an array.
It returns undefined when there's no value.
It returns the same array if the value is already an array.
It returns new array of the item is not an array.

methods.name: _getValue
methods.description: Gets a signle scalar value from a model.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _getValueArray
methods.description: Gets values from a model as an array of `@value` properties.

params.name: model
params.description: Amf model to extract the value from.

params.name: key
params.description: Model key to search for the value

methods.name: _hasType
methods.description: Checks if a model has a type.

return.desc: True if model has a type.

methods.name: _hasProperty
methods.description: Checks if a shape has a property.

methods.name: _computePropertyArray
methods.description: Computes array value of a property in a model (shape).

methods.name: _computePropertyObject
methods.description:
Computes a value of a property in a model (shape).
It takes first value of a property, if exists.

methods.name: _computeHasStringValue
methods.description: Tests if a passed argumet exists.

methods.name: _computeHasArrayValue
methods.description:
Computes if passed argument is an array and has a value.
It does not check for type or value of the array items.

methods.name: _computeDescription
methods.description: Computes description for a shape.

methods.name: _computeServerVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `serverVariables` property.

methods.name: _computeEndpointVariables
methods.description: Computes value for `endpointVariables` property.

methods.name: _computePayload
methods.description: Computes value for the `payload` property

methods.name: _computeReturns
methods.description: Computes value for `returns` property

methods.name: _computeSecurity
methods.description: Computes value for `security` property

methods.name: _computeHasCustomProperties
methods.description: Computes value for `hasCustomProperties` property.

methods.name: _computeApiVersion
methods.description: Computes API version from the AMF model.

methods.name: _computeEncodes
methods.description: Computes model's `encodes` property.

methods.name: _computeDeclares
methods.description: Computes list of declarations in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeReferences
methods.description: Computes list of references in the AMF api model.

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeWebApi
methods.description: Computes AMF's `http://schema.org/WebAPI` model

params.name: model
params.description: AMF json/ld model for an API

methods.name: _computeServer
methods.description: Computes value for `server` property that is later used with other computations.

methods.name: _computeEndpointUri
methods.description: Computes endpoint's URI based on `amfModel` and `endpoint` models.

methods.name: _getBaseUri
methods.description:
Computes base URI value from either `baseUri`, `iron-meta` with
`ApiBaseUri` key or `amfModel` value (in this order).

return.desc: Base uri value. Can be empty string.

methods.name: _getAmfBaseUri
methods.description: Computes base URI from AMF model.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
Listy of supporte dprotocols. If not
provided and required to compute the url it uses `amfModel` to compute
protocols

methods.name: _ensureUrlScheme
methods.description:
A function that makes sure that the URL has a scheme definition.
If no supported protocols information is available it assumes `http`.

params.name: protocols
params.description:
List of supported by the API protocols
An array of string like: `['HTTP', 'HTTPS']`. It lowercase the value.
If not set it tries to read supported protocols value from `amfModel`
property.

methods.name: _computeProtocols
methods.description: Computes supported protocols by the API.

methods.name: _computeExpects
methods.description: Computes value for the `expects` property.

methods.name: _computePropertyValue
methods.description:
Tries to find an example value (whether it's default value or from an
example) to put it into snippet's values.

methods.name: _computeEndpoints
methods.description: Computes list of endpoints from a WebApi model.

return.desc: Always returns an array of endpoints.

methods.name: _computeEndpointModel
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation.

methods.name: _computeEndpointByPath
methods.description: Computes model for an endpoint documentation using it's path.

methods.name: _computeMethodModel
methods.description: Computes method for the method documentation.

methods.name: _computeOperations
methods.description: Computes list of operations in an endpoint

methods.name: _computeMethodEndpoint
methods.description: Computes an endpoint for a method.

methods.name: __computeMethodsListForMethod
methods.description:
Computes a list of methods for an endpoint that contains a method with
given id.

return.desc: A list of sibling methods or undefined.

methods.name: _computeType
methods.description: Computes a type documentation model.

methods.name: _computeReferenceType
methods.description: Computes a type model from a reference (library for example).

params.name: reference
params.description: AMF model for a reference to extract the data from

return.desc: Type definition or undefined if not found.

methods.name: _computeSecurityModel
methods.description: Computes model for selected security definition.

methods.name: _computeDocument
methods.description: Computes a documentation model.

methods.name: _resolve
methods.description: Resolves a reference to an external fragment.

methods.name: _getExampleValue
methods.description: Gets string value for an example data model.

params.name: isJson
params.description:
If set it checks if the `raw` value is valid JSON.
If it isn't then it parses structured value.

methods.name: _computeExampleFromStructuredValue
methods.description: Computes an example from example structured value.

return.desc: Javascript object or array with structured value.

methods.name: _computeStructuredExampleValue
methods.description: Computes value with propert data type for a structured example.

methods.name: _modelLocationChanged
methods.description:
Loads model from a file described in `modelLocation` property.
This function is called automatically when the value of the property
change.

methods.name: _apiLoadEndHandler
methods.description: Called by `_modelLocationChanged` when model data are read from remote location.

methods.name: _apiLoadErrorHandler
methods.description: Called by `_modelLocationChanged` when error occurred when getting API data.

methods.name: _tryitHandler
methods.description:
Handler for the `tryit-requested` event. Sets current screen to
`request`.

methods.name: resetSelection
methods.description: Resets current selection to "summary" page

methods.name: _computeApiTitle
methods.description: Computes value of `apiTitle` property.

methods.name: _computeIsRequest
methods.description: Computes value for `isRequest` property.

methods.name: _computeIsDocs
methods.description: Computes value for `isDocs` property.

methods.name: _initExtensionBanner
methods.description: Renders the extension banner if is Chrome and extension is not detected.

methods.name: dismissExtensionBanner
methods.description: Dismisses Chrome extension banner.

methods.name: _apiNavigationOcurred
methods.description:
Handler for the navigation event dispatched by the `api-navigation`
component.

methods.name: closeTryIt
methods.description: Closes "try it" panel and restores docs view.

methods.name: _computeNarrowNavForced
methods.description: Computes value of `_narrowNavForced` property.

methods.name: resetLayout
methods.description:
When the console is initialized when being hidden
it may not layout properly. The app drawer layout component
positions elements statically so if the console is hidden it cannot do
this properly. In this case call `resetLayout()` function
when getting the console back from the hidden state.

methods.name: _notifyApicExtension
methods.description:
Dispatches `api-console-ready` event that is used by APIC extension
so it can initialize itself when handled

methods.name: _noExtBannerChanged
methods.description: Controls behavior if the extension banner.

methods.name: _computeIsMethod
methods.description: Computes value of `isMethod` proiperty.

return.desc: True if current selection represent a method

methods.name: _computeRenderInlineTryIt
methods.description: Computes value for `_renderInlineTyit` property.

return.desc:
True if is wideLayout, it is a method, it is the app
and when inlineMethods is not set.

methods.name: _computeMethodName
methods.description:
Computes method name for not-wide view, where the request panel
has close button.

return.desc:
Name of current method (verb) as RAML's
`displayName` property or name of the HTTP method.
